        "@id": "https://ww3.ticketpro.ca/event.php?event_id=10750"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/url": [
      {
        "@id": "https://ww3.ticketpro.ca/event.php?event_id=10750"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "Mary Frances"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>Having performed with her parents and acclaimed fiddlers Natalie MacMaster and Donnell Leahy for over 600 shows, genre-defying fiddling (and piano) sensation Mary Frances Leahy is branching out with her fantastic debut solo album First Light. The innovative, eclectic nine-track collection of originals, co-produced by Mary Frances and Cuban guitarist Elmer Ferrer, is an amazing blending of Celtic, Latin, and Jazz influences.</p>\n\n<p><i>'It's a bunch of styles you wouldn't think go well together,'</i> the Canadian phenom from the hamlet of Douro, Ontario says. <i>'But once you hear it, you're like, 'Oh my gosh, I get it!' My sound is energetic. It makes me want to dance!'</i> She isn't the only one. Whether it's the title track (which won a 2024 Cape Breton Tourism contest), the jazzy 'Return to Skye,' the alluring Latin-leaning 'Camino' which\nequally shows her violin and piano prowess or the groovy fusion oozing from 'Celticumbia,' Leahy is confident and charismatic from start to finish. <i>'The one thing I'm finding that's really cohesive between the genres is the role that dance plays with themusic,'</i> she says. <i>'I'm finding that to be a common thread.'</i></p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n"
      }
    ],
